<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1750,1992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1896" box="[151,423,1750,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachylepidalis">
<emphasis box="[151,423,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Locastra pachylepidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an exception to the above grouping and is distinct from all its other congeners by the absence of the costal lobe and the scape extension. The placement of this species in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1209,1309,1787,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1209,1309,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Locastra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is doubtful and needs to be studied through examination of the male and female genitalia.
</paragraph>
